717628f-a.text: The Ansonia, Broadway, west side from 73rd to 74th Streets. This building will still stand in 1936. About 1904.

717626f-a.text: The United States Mortgage and Trust Company, 2095-2099 Broadway at the S. W. corner of 73rd Street, which between 1920 and 1925 replaced the Rutgers Presbyterian Church. The new church is seen at the right, on 73rd Street, on the site of the chapel of the old. About 1925. Drix Duryea.

The view includes the west side of Broadway from 74th to 76th Streets, the west side of Amsterdam Avenue from 73rd to 75th Streets, and the north side of 74th Street from Amsterdam Avenue to Broadway. At the extreme left is the Ansonia, an old apartment hotel. At the right is the Hotel Prisament. June 25, 1927. Gift of York & Sawyer.
